<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p><img src="https://github.com/xndbogdan/statamic-bard-text-color/raw/main/preview_v5.0.1.png" alt="alt text" title="Preview"></p>
<p>This is a statamic bard plugin that lets you change text color!
It allows you to use the default tailwind palette, but you can also add your own.
At the moment it's still under development, so please report any bugs that you encounter.
New feature suggestions are welcomed too.</p>
<h2>Getting started</h2>
<p>If you only wish to use the default tailwind palette, then it's as easy as running the composer require command.</p>
<p><code>composer require xndbogdan/statamic-bard-text-color</code></p>
<h2>Custom colors</h2>
<h3>Using a config file</h3>
<p>The simplest way of adding new colors to this plugin is by adding a  <code>bard-custom-colors.php</code>  config file to your project.
Please check <a href="https://github.com/xndbogdan/statamic-bard-text-color/blob/main/config/bard-custom-colors.php">this</a> file if you need an example.</p>
<h2>Planned features</h2>
<ul>
<li>Pull colors from tailwind.config.js automatically</li>
<li>Upgrade to Vue 3</li>
<li>Upgrade to Vite</li>
</ul>
